Kernel; 
It is the core of the linux operating system. The kernel is responsible for managing core components of a system like CPU, RAM and Storage. It is the third layer in linux architecture. 
User space;
This section comprises of first two layers of linux architecture (Application and Shell). This is where user runs all the applications, utilities and talks to the kernel via shell.
init/systemd
Init;
 is a system program that is initiated by kernel when system is turned on. Init is responsible for starting the important services like networking, login screens, and background system tasks. 
Systemd;
is an advanced version of init which ensure the smooth running of the the important services including to restart the services if needed. networking, login screens, and background system tasks
Processes are created using the fork() and exec() mechanisms.
“In linux every user process comes from another process.”
